                    text: "The most common issues are high-pressure fuel pump failure, DPF clogging, EGR cooler failure, and turbo actuator sticking. These are documented in Jaguar service bulletins and field reports. HPFP and DPF problems arise from low-quality fuel and short-trip driving, while EGR and turbo faults are linked to carbon buildup. Fuel pump longevity depends on fuel lubricity and filtration.",
